pixa.providers.markdownDescription:
Add your own model providers. Works with **any OpenAI-compatible endpoint** — a cloud API, a company gateway, or a self-hosted server (Ollama, vLLM, LM Studio, llama.cpp). After adding one, run **Pixa: Set Provider API Key** (skip for local servers with `requiresApiKey: false`). Models appear in the chat picker as `provider:model`.

**Example — self-hosted Ollama (no key needed):**
```json
"pixa.providers": {
  "ollama": {
    "name": "Ollama (local)",
    "baseUrl": "http://localhost:11434/v1",
    "requiresApiKey": false,
    "models": { "qwen2.5-coder": { "name": "Qwen2.5 Coder", "contextWindow": 32768 } }
  }
}
```

**Example — NVIDIA NIM:**
```json
"pixa.providers": {
  "nvidia": {
    "name": "NVIDIA NIM",
    "baseUrl": "https://integrate.api.nvidia.com/v1",
    "models": { "z-ai/glm-5.2": { "name": "GLM 5.2", "contextWindow": 128000 } }
  }
}
```
